@baseUrl = https://localhost:7038

### 1. Get all books (with availability status)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/books
Accept: application/json

### 2. Check out an available book (book 1) to member 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 1,
  "memberId": 1
}

### 3. Try to check out the same book again (should return 409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bookId": 1,
  "memberId": 2
}

### 4. Return the checkout we just created (id will be 10 — first generated id)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/10/return
Accept: application/json

### 5. Get all overdue checkouts (checkout id 1 is seeded as overdue)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/overdue
Accept: application/json

### 6. Dashboard stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/checkouts/dashboard
Accept: application/json
